</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>};
</span></span></code></pre></div><h2 id="34-prefix-sum">3.4 Prefix Sum</h2>
<p>Caculate sum of subarray in O(1)</p>
<p>index        0  1  2   3   4   5
nums   =    [5, 2, 1,  6,  3,  8]
|&lt;&mdash;&ndash;&gt;|
prefix = [0, 5, 7, 8, 14, 17, 25]</p>
<p>sum(nums[i: j)) = prefix[j] - prefix[i]
ex. sum(nums[0:3)) = prefix[3] - prefix[0] = 8 - 0 = 8</p>
<h3 id="calculate-prefix-sum">Calculate prefix sum</h3>
<pre tabindex="0"><code>Given an array nums,

prefix = [0]
for (int i = 0; i &lt; nums.length; i++)
    prefix.append(prefix[prefix.length - 1] + nums[i])
</code></pre><h3 id="complexity">Complexity</h3>
<p>A prefix sum is a great tool whenever a problem involves sums of a subarray.</p>
<p>It only costs O(n) to build but allows all future subarray queries to be O(1), so it can usually improve an algorithm&rsquo;s time complexity by a factor of O(n), where n is the length of the array.</p>
<h3 id="ex1-prefix-sum">Ex1. Prefix Sum</h3>
<p>Given an integer array nums, an array queries where queries[i] = [x, y] and an integer limit, return a boolean array that represents the answer to each query.
A query is true if the sum of the subarray from x to y is less than limit, or false otherwise.</p>
<p>For example, given nums = [1, 6, 3, 2, 7, 2], queries = [[0, 3], [2, 5], [2, 4]], and limit = 13,
the answer is [true, false, true]. For each query, the subarray sums are [12, 14, 12].</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-C++" data-lang="C++"><span style="display:flex;"><span>vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span><span style="color:#66d9ef">bool</span><span style="color:#f92672">&gt;</span> answerQueries(vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span><span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span><span style="color:#f92672">&gt;&amp;</span> nums, vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span>vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span><span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span><span style="color:#f92672">&gt;&gt;&amp;</span> queries, <span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> limit) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span><span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span><span style="color:#f92672">&gt;</span> prefix <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> {<span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>};
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    <span style="color:#66d9ef">for</span> (<span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> i <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>; i <span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span> nums.size(); i<span style="color:#f92672">++</span>) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        prefix.push_back(prefix.back() <span style="color:#f92672">+</span> nums[i]);
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    }
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span><span style="color:#66d9ef">bool</span><span style="color:#f92672">&gt;</span> ans;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    <span style="color:#66d9ef">for</span> (vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span><span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span><span style="color:#f92672">&gt;&amp;</span> query: queries) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> x <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> query[<span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>], y <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> query[<span style="color:#ae81ff">1</span>];
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> curr <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> prefix[y <span style="color:#f92672">+</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">1</span>] <span style="color:#f92672">-</span> prefix[x];
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        ans.push_back(curr <span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span> limit);
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    }
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    <span style="color:#66d9ef">return</span> ans;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>}
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// Without the prefix sum, answering each query would be O(n) in the worst case, where n is the length of nums. 
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// If m = queries.length, that would give a time complexity of O(n * m). 
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e"></span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// With the prefix sum, it costs O(n) to build, but then answering each query is O(1). 
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// This gives a much better time complexity of O(n + m). 
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e"></span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// We use O(n) space to build the prefix sum.
</span></span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="ex2-number-of-ways-to-split-array">Ex2. Number of ways to split array</h3>
<p>nums = [1, 6, 3, 2, 7, 2]</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-C++" data-lang="C++"><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#66d9ef">class</span> <span style="color:#a6e22e">Solution</span> {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#66d9ef">public</span><span style="color:#f92672">:</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    <span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> waysToSplitArray(vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span><span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span><span style="color:#f92672">&gt;&amp;</span> nums) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> n <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> nums.size();
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span><span style="color:#66d9ef">long</span><span style="color:#f92672">&gt;</span> prefix <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> {<span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>};
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">for</span> (<span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> i <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>; i <span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span> n; i<span style="color:#f92672">++</span>) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            prefix.push_back(nums[i] <span style="color:#f92672">+</span> prefix.back());
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        }
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> ans <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">for</span> (<span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> i <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">1</span>; i <span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span> n; i<span style="color:#f92672">++</span>) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            <span style="color:#66d9ef">long</span> leftSection <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> prefix[i];
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            <span style="color:#66d9ef">long</span> rightSection <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> prefix.back() <span style="color:#f92672">-</span> prefix[i];
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            <span style="color:#66d9ef">if</span> (leftSection <span style="color:#f92672">&gt;=</span> rightSection) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>                ans<span style="color:#f92672">++</span>;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            }
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        }
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">return</span> ans;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    }
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>};
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// Do we need the array? No.
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// leftSection = 0 
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// leftSection += nums[i]
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// 
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// rightSection = total - leftSection
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e">// We have improved the space complexity to O(1)
</span></span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e"></span><span style="color:#66d9ef">class</span> <span style="color:#a6e22e">Solution</span> {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#66d9ef">public</span><span style="color:#f92672">:</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    <span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> waysToSplitArray(vector<span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span><span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span><span style="color:#f92672">&gt;&amp;</span> nums) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> ans <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">long</span> leftSection <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">long</span> total <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">for</span> (<span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> num: nums) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            total <span style="color:#f92672">+=</span> num;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        }
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">for</span> (<span style="color:#66d9ef">int</span> i <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">0</span>; i <span style="color:#f92672">&lt;</span> nums.size() <span style="color:#f92672">-</span> <span style="color:#ae81ff">1</span>; i<span style="color:#f92672">++</span>) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            leftSection <span style="color:#f92672">+=</span> nums[i];
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            <span style="color:#66d9ef">long</span> rightSection <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> total <span style="color:#f92672">-</span> leftSection;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            <span style="color:#66d9ef">if</span> (leftSection <span style="color:#f92672">&gt;=</span> rightSection) {
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>                ans<span style="color:#f92672">++</span>;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>            }
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        }
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>        <span style="color:#66d9ef">return</span> ans;
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>    }
